column49: 1) Because the catalog cycle doesn’t reset until Nov 17th, I’m not able to get the $10 of free books for my room that I earned. I called customer service about this, as the site was telling me I earned this reward. I just couldn’t select the reward.    2) I’ve noticed fewer new book selections between the catalogs, which isn’t ideal.    3) The glue binding that the catalogs are secured with are a pain to get off, and then I have to separate in 2 catalogs. Bring back the staples. At least those would come out and nothing had to be separated.    4) I do not like that the catalogs are promoting more items this year that aren’t books (i.e. pens, keychains,  etc.) and that the catalogs are filled with random activities.    I’ll see what the next catalog entails in 2024, but if these things continue,  I won’t be ordering much in the future.

I also hate that there are very few $1 or $2 books. Unfortunately, many families will not buy anymore due to the lack of cheaper books. The other issue is that you don't have many books available at a lower cost. We are an urban district and parents would be more likely to order if the book prices were more helpful for them. This year has been the worst so far.

column49: I am very disappointed in Scholastic this year.  Myself and many other teachers have gotten donations for years so that we can provide book donations for students.  We do this so that students who do not have books at home can have them and we provide books for all students.  This year the lowest price I can find is $2.99.  My students will have very few books with my donations this year and I doubt I will do the donations again.      This will mean I will spend hundreds less on Scholastic from now on.  I typically get $300-$400 worth of donations each year but the money just won't stretch far enough to make the work with it for me.  I am deeply saddened about this as I have enjoyed doing this each year for my students.

Every year I had my friends and family donate money so that I could purchase books for my students to take home every month. Now I cant afford to do that. This is a huge let down because there are so many students do not have the luxury to have a lot of books at home, so it was very beneficial for them. Now I can only afford to send a few home. The $2 option books are not even great options, as I teach kindergarten, and I can't sent home a chapter book. I feel like the scholastic website has gone downhill. Books used to be reasonably priced.

column49: Although I do enjoy the quality of the books, I am not happy with the flyer dates. I typically place an order each month. This year, I only have 6 chances and I do not have the flexibility to choose my own dates. My second parent order is due on November 8th and my third is due on November 29th. This means that I am asking for orders before a previous order has been delivered. This does not make me feel comfortable knowing that many families might not be able to order. Having an order in September to get kids excited about reading at the beginning of the year and another in November to ship before the holidays makes much more sense.   I have noticed a huge drop off of parental orders which in turn affects my ordering as I do not earn as many points. I use those points to build my library and to gift books. Again, building the excitement of reading one book at a time.

column49: Changing the way teachers place their order on this site is completely ridiculous. As a very busy teacher, it's hard enough finding time to pass out flyers and get the due date, etc. ready on my end. But now I just discovered you're setting my due dates for me. I'm very disappointed in Scholastic making this inconvenient change.

column49: I’m really disappointed in the changes that have been made with the company. The Club Leo catalogs aren’t available anymore and a very limited amount of Spanish bilingual books are available online. Our school demographic is 90% Spanish speaking and sending out the new Scholastic catalogs doesn’t make them feel included or represented with there only being English books available in the catalogs. Many do not order online and order with us staff so asking them to come in just to order Spanish books so they can see what’s available online isn’t equitable.     Secondly, the prices of books have gone up tremendously. As a teacher, my coworker, and I would buy hundreds of books from your website to give to our students as gifts throughout the year. We were easily able to find $ 1- 2 books to buy in large quantities to gift to our students. We often purchased so much and had access to the dollar club access after spending a certain amount.  We were thankful to be able to buy more b

column49: I am quite angry at the new system that you have set this year.  I work in a residential school- so the children live here (not having contact with parents each day)  The students bring me the money and I order for them- NOW I have no way of knowing which children ordered what because you have taken away the name.  WHY? It would be so helpful to just add the name- also the tax and the prices being not rounded out? This is all sooo extremely difficult and I end up using my OWN money to pay the tax.  Yet again another thing the teacher just pays out of pocket.  Why would i continue to use your site, when we could easily use amazon or another site that doesn't make this SO difficult.
